The '''teleportation trap''' is a [[trap]] that can teleport you to a different location on the map.

==Generation==
Teleportation traps can be generated almost anywhere except non-teleport levels.

Special "vault teleporters" are sometimes generated in a [[closet]] behind an ''[[ad aerarium]]'' engraving. However, such closets might have a [[level teleporter]] instead.

==Effects==
These traps can affect you{{refsrc|src/trap.c|1302|nethack=3.6.6}}{{refsrc|src/teleport.c|1065|nethack=3.6.6}} or a monster{{refsrc|src/trap.c|2522|nethack=3.6.6}}{{refsrc|src/teleport.c|1306|nethack=3.6.6}}.

The destination is a random point on the current level, unless it is a [[vault]] teleporter, in which case you are teleported to the vault.

[[Magic resistance]] will prevent you from being teleported. If you want to use the teleporter (for instance, to enter a vault), you may use {{kbd|ctrl|t}} to take the teleporter despite magic resistance. A vault teleporter will give you a warning before triggering. If one of the squares in the vault is occupied by a monster or a trap (including the portal to [[Fort Ludios]]) or is otherwise unsafe, the vault teleport may fail, in which case the trap will act as an ordinary teleport trap, albeit single-use.{{refsrc|src/teleport.c|746|nethack=3.6.6}}

==Strategy==
To avoid unintentionally levelporting, you should not blindly walk into a closet without identifying the trap first.

==Removal==
Dig a pit on the same square and fill it with a boulder. If the trap is located behind an ''ad aerarium'' engraving, it will disappear after successfully teleporting the player. Monsters cannot use it up.

{{upcoming|NetHack 3.7.0|Teleportation traps can be removed by zapping them with the spell or wand of cancellation. The trap will explode for 23 to 38 damage.}}

==Messages==
{{message|You jump onto the teleportation trap.|You used {{kbd|ctrl|t}} to trigger a teleport trap.}}
{{message|This is a vault teleport, usable once only.  Jump in? [yn]|As above, but for a vault teleport trap and you have a chance to refuse.}}
{{message|You feel a wrenching sensation.|Magic resistance prevented you from being teleported.}}
{{message|<monster> seems disoriented.|A monster teleported and you saw it reach its destination.}}
{{message|<monster> suddenly disappears!|A monster teleported and you did not see it reach its destination.}}
{{message|Suddenly the rolling boulder disappears!|A boulder rolled onto a teleport trap and teleported away.}}
{{message|You hear a rumbling stop abruptly.|As above, but you could not see the boulder.}}

